EXTRA NOTES FOR PRACTICAL 9:
================================================================
- For Send Mail: always test with your own email first (both To and From 
  set to the same Gmail) so you can see the result immediately.
- Hotkey Trigger keeps the robot alive in background — it won't stop 
  unless you manually stop it or add a specific stop condition.
- Exception Handling is CRUCIAL for professional automation. 
  Without it, one unexpected error crashes your entire workflow.
- Try Catch in UiPath = try-catch-finally in Python/Java — same concept.
- The "Throw" activity lets you manually raise exceptions too
